<!-- Node: "MOD development tutorials" -->
<div class="body_box_header">MOD development tutorials</div>
<div class="body_box"><small>Submitted by <a href="http://www.gamedesign.net/user/view/2" title="View user profile.">Gard</a> on Wednesday, May 5, 2004 - 01:53</small><br /><br />
<p>I don't want to advertise ... but I followed the <a href="http://soldner.jowood.com/?RubrikIdentifier=961&lang=en">"SOLDNER: Secret War"</a> advert link to their home page. I discovered 6 tutorials documenting the steps the developers went through to create the game. It was a very good read, well written, good presentation, and clearly describes each step in MOD development. The tutorials do lack a detailed technical description of the issues faced at every step. However, it does provide a realistic overview of the task you have to accomplish when making a MOD. Too often people pop onto the RUST forums with a so-called great MOD idea, and want someone to help model the weapons. There must be more weapons for failed models than any other part of the game. The <a href="http://soldner.jowood.com/?RubrikIdentifier=961&lang=en">"SOLDNER: Secret War"</a> development tutorials puts MOD developments steps in the right order (you don't make the guns first!). So it is a good read if you are planning to make your own game. I liked.
